<p class = 'introduction'>
  Building an electric circuit always has a risk:
  if the current in the circuit is too high, the circuit will
  overheat and potentially start a fire.
  The risk is low if you are building circuits with only D batteries,
  but it much higher if you are using devices that require high amounts of voltage
  and current.
  Fortunately, there is a device that protects your circuit from dangerous levels
  of current: a fuse.
  A fuse is a device that burns up if the current in a circuit reaches a certain level.
</p>


